UObjectToolTips.QuestInstanceInitializationData:
When qs2 quest managers grant and initialize a new quest instance, all properties from this data bundle (taken post-initialization)
will be replicated from the server quest instance and injected back into the client quest instance as part of its creation and initialization
This allows us to guarantee certain data will be present on a client quest instance before any post-creation logic executes
It also provides a route for non-deterministic 'server authoritative' state to be routed to a client. (e.g. 'Randomly chosen' objectives also conditional on server world state)

UObjectToolTips.FortProjectileMoveComp_Slider:bSuspensio:
When set to true allows downward tension to be added on deflection and eased every tick. Downward tension is built up when the projectile gains downward velocity after a deflection, downward tension will add upward velocity to the projectile over time; might be useful to minimize jumping curbs in uncommon gravity situations.
     Turning this on can cause the projectile to build up suspension while sliding on the ground and cause it to jump, especially if a lot of gravity gets dumped into the velocity during a fire rate spike.
     If disabled tension will not update nor build in the downward direction. Tension will ease every frame as long as bSuspensionEnabled_Up or bSuspensionEnabled_Down is enabled.

When set to true allows upward tension to be added on deflection and eased every tick. Upward tension is built up when the projectile gains upward velocity after a deflection, upward tension will add downward velocity to the projectile over time; this is a good way to minimize jumping curbs.
     If disabled tension will not update nor build in the upward direction. Tension will ease every frame as long as bSuspensionEnabled_Up or bSuspensionEnabled_Down is enabled.

UObjectToolTips.FortGeneratePropertyPathData:NestedPrope:
When using auto property path generation to generate path to a property that's either inside a map or an array.
We expect to have a valid index for that property to be added to this map via AddGeneratePathPropertyNestedIndexData
Example lets say you are looking for property bCount for Objective 2 the path would be Objectives[2]->bCount
Auto generation how ever doesn't know it has to look for Index = 2. So in this case we need to specify that for Property Objectives we are looking for Index 2
In case of maps the property path also use Indexes. You can generate an array of keys using maps GenerateKeyArray function.
Then find the key you are looking for inside that array and get it's index. That would be the index the property index data expects

UObjectToolTips.UIStateSettings:WidgetStateComponentUnlo:
Widget State Components that are set to "Wait For Animations" will wait up to this many seconds when transitioning out of their States.
If the timeout is reached then the transition will proceed even if animations have not completed. This is to prevent a misconfigured
widget from soft-locking the game.
UObjectToolTips.UIStateSettings:WidgetStateComponentLoad:
Widget State Components will wait up to this many seconds for their widget classes to load when transitioning into their States.
If the timeout is reached then the transition will proceed even if the widgets are not ready. This is to prevent load errors
or related problems from soft-locking the game.

UObjectToolTips.GrantQuestBlueprintParameters:QuestParti:
[Optional] If set, the subsystem will attempt to grant the quest to the quest manager associated with this participation scope
If not set, the subsystem will attempt to grant the quest through auditing its data to see where what manager it likely belongs to
(i.e. a quest definition with a shared quest component will end up be granted to a team/squad/party quest manager)
UObjectToolTips.EffectRequestContext:ContextTags: [Optional] Tags describing the context in which the request was made e.g. (Freebie gift type tag, Game Mode, POI etc)
UObjectToolTips.EffectRequestContext:SourceTags: [Optional] Tags related to any logical 'Source'/'Requester' of the effect e.g. (Unique ServiceProviderID Tag)
UObjectToolTips.EffectRequestContext:TargetTags: [Optional] Tags related to any logical 'Target' of the effect request e.g. (Player tags)
UObjectToolTips.GrantQuestBlueprintParameters:Instigator:
[Optional] The object that instigated this quest grant event and should be used for quest scoping
For example, if a player is passed in as the Instigator and the quest is marked to be a squad quest,
then the quest will be granted to the Instigator's squad.
If bInstigatorOwnsQuest is marked true, then the Instigator will also be treated as the QuestOwner
UObjectToolTips.GrantQuestBlueprintParameters:bInstigato:
[Optional] True if the passed in Instigator should have ownership over the newly granted quest
If true, the newly granted quest will attempt to export progression to the Instigator through our backend services
(i.e. a player exporting their quest progress to MCP)

UObjectToolTips.FortGameModeAthena:bEnableCompetitiveDDo:
enable ending matches early if we detect a given number of escalations to the given DDoS severity (see engine config [DDoSDetection] for tiers)
within a given time threshold after we end aircraft phase. the above detections should limit the effectiveness of DDoS attacks in warmup and aircraft,
but we can't have such clearly defined behavior detection during the course of a match for a number of reasons. that being said, we can determine
analytically the threshold at which a match is _almost certainly_ being DDosed during safezones and kill it to take away their candy.
UObjectToolTips.FortGameStateComponent_BattleRoyaleGameP:
enable ending matches early if we detect abnormalities in the number of players alive both at the start and end of aircraft phase.
for this to happen, either the internet is on fire or someone is trying to DDoS the server. in any case, we do not want the match to count.

are used to display the tree in the editor UI. A separate structure represents the tree at runtime.

Class defining branch elements in a binary decision tree displayed in the editor UI only.
Each branch contains two children (true and false) and a the name of a property that can
be used to look up a boolean condition in the runtime structure.
UObjectToolTips.LogicTreeLeaf:
struct FLogicTreeLeaf

Class defining the final, leaf elements in a binary decision tree displayed in the editor UI only.
